ce:section.ce:para:
To measure the biological application potential of the LW-CDs, we performed cellular imaging using Hela cells. When the cells completed incubating, the cells were washed by PBS (pH = 7.4) three times to remove other substances. To measure the capacity of monitoring intracellular pH variation, cellular images were took while cells were treated by PBS solution with different pH value(4, 7 and 9) and LW-CDs. The result showed that with the increase of pH value, the fluorescence intensity of Hela cells gradually decreased(Fig. 6
                        ). Then we took two set of cells. One was treated with PBS solution(pH = 7.4) and LW-CDs, and the other was treated with PBS solution, LW-CDs and ClO-(0.5 mM). As shown in Fig. 7
                        , the fluorescence intensity of Hela cells with ClO- showed significant decay. Those results implied the LW-CDs had biological application potential to monitor pH and ClO- concentration.
